The tissues and organs, it would appear, retain
in the resurrection their static entity, but part with
many of their dynamic functions. There is still to be
seen, I think, at Darlington Station one of Stephenson's 
first engines, erected on a pedestal. The parallel
is not exact, but suggestive.


